{
  "id": "service-accounts.service-account-audit-preview",
  "title": "Service account audit preview",
  "version": 1,
  "kind": "SduiWidget",
  "description": "Compact 30-day audit preview: request-count histogram sparkline + distinct-IP-/24-prefix count + jti-reuse detection count. Renders on the SA show screen; requires `platform.service_accounts.view.audit_trail` permission. Hidden when permission missing. Full report (heavier query with per-request rows) lives behind the audit-usage endpoint.",
  "props": {
    "usage": {
      "type": "object",
      "required": true,
      "description": "ServiceAccountUsageReportData shape (see data-classes.json). Contains: histogram, distinct_ip_prefix_count, jti_reuse_count, total_requests, distinct_audiences."
    },
    "size": {
      "type": "string",
      "enum": ["sm", "md"],
      "required": false,
      "default": "sm"
    }
  },
  "requiresPermission": "platform.service_accounts.view.audit_trail",
  "render": {
    "kind": "View",
    "props": { "className": "flex flex-col gap-2 mt-2" },
    "children": [
      {
        "kind": "Sparkline",
        "props": {
          "height": 40,
          "color": "primary"
        },
        "bindings": {
          "data": { "$ref": "props.usage.histogram" }
        }
      },
      {
        "kind": "View",
        "props": { "className": "flex items-center gap-4 text-xs" },
        "children": [
          {
            "kind": "View",
            "props": { "className": "flex flex-col" },
            "children": [
              { "kind": "Text", "props": { "className": "text-muted", "children": "30d requests" } },
              {
                "kind": "Text",
                "props": { "className": "font-medium" },
                "bindings": { "children": { "$ref": "props.usage.total_requests" } }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "kind": "View",
            "props": { "className": "flex flex-col" },
            "children": [
              { "kind": "Text", "props": { "className": "text-muted", "children": "Distinct IP /24s" } },
              {
                "kind": "Text",
                "props": { "className": "font-medium" },
                "bindings": { "children": { "$ref": "props.usage.distinct_ip_prefix_count" } }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "kind": "View",
            "props": { "className": "flex flex-col" },
            "children": [
              { "kind": "Text", "props": { "className": "text-muted", "children": "Distinct audiences" } },
              {
                "kind": "Text",
                "props": { "className": "font-medium" },
                "bindings": { "children": { "$ref": "props.usage.distinct_audiences" } }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "kind": "View",
            "props": { "className": "flex flex-col" },
            "children": [
              { "kind": "Text", "props": { "className": "text-muted", "children": "jti-reuse detections" } },
              {
                "kind": "Text",
                "props": { "className": "font-medium" },
                "bindings": {
                  "children": { "$ref": "props.usage.jti_reuse_count" },
                  "props": {
                    "className": {
                      "$expr": "props.usage.jti_reuse_count > 0 ? 'text-danger font-medium' : 'font-medium'"
                    }
                  }
                }
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "kind": "Link",
        "props": {
          "to": "/platform/service-accounts/{id}/audit-usage",
          "className": "text-xs text-primary",
          "children": "View full report \u2192"
        }
      }
    ]
  },
  "notes": [
    "jti-reuse count > 0 is a compromise-adjacent signal \u2014 legitimate SA traffic never re-uses a jti because each JWT gets a fresh UUID at issue. The widget highlights this in danger text.",
    "The sparkline shows request count per 24h bucket over 30 days; spikes correlate with fleet scale-out (benign) OR compromised-credential replay (malignant). Full attribution via the audit-usage report."
  ]
}
